    <text type="letter" xml:lang="ru" xml:id="letter-09002">
        <body>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <date when-custom="1784-04-24">1784 г. 24 апреля.</date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Александр Васильевич,</salute>
            </opener>
            <p>прикажи выписать из <title ref="works.xml#rodosl01">бархатной книги</title>
                <note type="editorial">
                    Catherine must have been using a 17th-century manuscript version of the book. The book was published by <persName ref="people.xml#nov01">Nikolai Ivanovich Novikov</persName> in 1787 under the title <title>"Rodoslovnaia kniga Kniazei i Dvorian rossiiskikh i vyezzhich"</title>
                </note>, 
                буде в <rs ref="works.xml#rodosl01">ней</rs> есть, о <orgName ref="orgs.xml#lans01">роде Ланских</orgName> и привези ко мне.
                <note type="editorial">
                    <bibl>
                        <title ref="works.xml#sobstv02">Sobstvennoruchnyia pis'ma i zapiski imperatritsy Ekateriny II k A. V. Khranovitskomu, 1783-1793</title> (
                        <biblScope unit="pp">pp. 4-5.</biblScope>)
                    </bibl>
                    suggests that Catherine might have wanted to accord some title to her favourite <persName ref="people.xml#lan02">Aleksandr Dmitrievich Lanskoi</persName>, who was already sick at the moment and died later on <date when-custom="1784-06-25">June 25 1784</date>.
                </note></p>
        </body>
